					&lt;pre style=&quot;font-size: 1em; margin: 0 10px;   margin-bottom: 10px;  width: auto; padding: 0;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: black; font-family: &apos;Consolas&apos;, &apos;Bitstream Vera Sans Mono&apos;, &apos;Courier New&apos;, Courier, monospace !important;&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
			&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p/&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Have a look: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.google.com/codesearch#SfNcgPiEUEg/trunk/dbdeploy-core/src/main/java/com/dbdeploy/database/QueryStatementSplitter.java&amp;amp;type=cs&amp;amp;q=delimiter%20package:http://dbdeploy%5C.googlecode%5C.com&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.google.com/codesearch#SfNcgPiEUEg/trunk/dbdeploy-core/src/main/java/com/dbdeploy/database/QueryStatementSplitter.java&amp;amp;type=cs&amp;amp;q=delimiter%20package:http://dbdeploy%5C.googlecode%5C.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="72918" author="cbeams" created="Mon, 21 Nov 2011 14:44:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Julian,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The concept of a configurable delimiter type makes sense.  This would need to be introduced on a script-by-script basis, e.g. signatures of &lt;tt&gt;addScript&lt;/tt&gt; methods on &lt;tt&gt;EmbeddedDatabaseBuilder&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;ResourceDatabasePopulator&lt;/tt&gt; would have to be introduced something like the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;addScript(Resource)&lt;/tt&gt; (existing signature)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;addScript(Resource, DelimiterType)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;where &lt;tt&gt;DelimiterType&lt;/tt&gt; is possibly an enum indicating end-of-line or end-of-file.  The default delimiter type would be end of line.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is just a sketch, but already would require fairly significant changes to the way that script resources are tracked and processed, and it&apos;s not yet clear whether such an addition would benefit enough users to go ahead with it.  In the meantime, and as you mention above, one can always use a JdbcTemplate or other means to add the statement, so there is a reasonable workaround here.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For these reasons, I&apos;ve moved this issue to the General Backlog and labeled it as &apos;under-consideration&apos;.  This gives it some time to catch additional attention, get votes, etc.  We&apos;ll certainly return to this if it proves popular, and in the meantime, it&apos;s a good candidate for a patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="72928" author="golliwog" created="Tue, 22 Nov 2011 02:42:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Chris,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the delimiter type could be added as a general setting in the ResourceDatabasePopulator (as it is in dbdeploy). This would make the implementation much easier.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="72937" author="cbeams" created="Tue, 22 Nov 2011 11:04:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Julian,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This could be a setting on &lt;tt&gt;ResourceDatabasePopulator&lt;/tt&gt;, but this assumes that all scripts added against that populator would have one delimiter type vs. another.  If I understand your own use case correctly, you have a mix, where one file has end-of-line and another has end-of-file.  Even if this is not your use case, one can imagine that it would be common (assuming this is a common need at all).  I am imagining a situation in which users have typical schema creation and data population scripts (end-of-line delimited), and the occasional sproc definition or other multi-line script necessitating end-of-file delimiter.  Do you agree?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="118915" author="sbrannen" created="Thu, 27 Aug 2015 15:01:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue is related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-13389&quot; title=&quot;Support triggers &amp;amp; stored procedures alongside standard statements in SQL scripts&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-13389&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-13389&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="118917" author="sbrannen" created="Thu, 27 Aug 2015 15:05:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FYI: an &lt;tt&gt;EOF_STATEMENT_SEPARATOR&lt;/tt&gt; was introduced in &lt;tt&gt;ScriptUtils&lt;/tt&gt; in Spring Framework 4.0.4 (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-11687&quot; title=&quot;Support EOF as statement separator in SQL scripts&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-11687&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-11687&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;ScriptUtils.EOF_STATEMENT_SEPARATOR&lt;/tt&gt; can naturally be supplied as the &lt;tt&gt;separator&lt;/tt&gt; (i.e., statement separator/delimiter) in:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;#8211; &lt;tt&gt;ScriptUtils.executeSqlScript(Connection, EncodedResource, boolean, boolean, String, String, String, String)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;#8211; &lt;tt&gt;ResourceDatabasePopulator.setSeparator(String)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;#8211; &lt;tt&gt;EmbeddedDatabaseBuilder.setSeparator(String)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="120418" author="sbrannen" created="Thu, 8 Oct 2015 18:21:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Due to lack of interest from the community and the existing support for an &lt;tt&gt;EOF_STATEMENT_SEPARATOR&lt;/tt&gt; that was introduced in &lt;tt&gt;ScriptUtils&lt;/tt&gt; in Spring Framework 4.0.4 (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-11687&quot; title=&quot;Support EOF as statement separator in SQL scripts&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-11687&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-11687&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), I am closing this issue as &lt;em&gt;Won&apos;t Fix&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
